{"title":"Cervélo LinkLock Lockout Turns ZFS-5 XC Bike into a Hardtail for XCC Short Track Racing","link":"https://bikerumor.com/cervelo-linklock-converts-xco-zfs-5-full-suspension-xc-mtb-bike-into-xcc-hardtail/","date":1684013434000,"content":"<p>Cervélo only officially revealed their new carbon <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/cervelo-zfs-5-carbon-full-suspension-xc-mountain-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">ZFS-5 full-suspension</a> cross-country race mountain bike a few days ago, and they’ve already shown how the Jumbo-Visma team used a rigid LinkLock to convert it back to a hardtail! Unbolt the short link, remove the standard RockShox SIDLuxe Ultimate shock &amp; its remote, then bolt in a peculiar wishbone strut in its place.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But why?</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Cervélo LinkLock converts XCO ZFS fully into an XCC hardtail</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_World-Cup-Short-Tack-race.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_World-Cup-Short-Tack-race-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Cervelo ZFS-5 LinkLock prototype lockout gadget, XCO full-suspension to XCC hardtail conversion, Milan Vader racing\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_World-Cup-Short-Tack-race-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_World-Cup-Short-Tack-race-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_World-Cup-Short-Tack-race-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_World-Cup-Short-Tack-race-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_World-Cup-Short-Tack-race-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_World-Cup-Short-Tack-race-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_World-Cup-Short-Tack-race.jpg 1800w\" /></a><figcaption><em>all photos by Cory Benson, copyright Bikerumor.com</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The “<em>why</em>” is “<em>because UCI</em>“. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The governing body of pro mountain bike racing, the UCI MTB World Cup rules require that cross-country racers must compete in the XCC short track race on the same bike as they ride in the main event Olympic-distance XCO cross-country race. But a closer look at the rules actually only specifies that it must be the same frame. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Individual components – like those that can be removed or replaced on the frame… for example wheels, tires, and gearing – are allowed to be swapped out to adapt the bike to the shorter, faster, and less technical nature of the short-track circuit racing. So while some racers would simply lock out their rear shock for the duration of the half hour XCC race – why not take it to the next level.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_with-or-without-suspension.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_with-or-without-suspension-800x450.jpg\" alt=\"Cervelo ZFS-5 LinkLock prototype lockout gadget, XCO full-suspension to XCC hardtail conversion, with or without rear suspension\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_with-or-without-suspension-800x450.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_with-or-without-suspension-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_with-or-without-suspension-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_with-or-without-suspension-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_with-or-without-suspension-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_with-or-without-suspension-400x225.jpg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_with-or-without-suspension-1200x675.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_with-or-without-suspension.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, Cervélo engineers worked with the Jumbo-Visma team to devise a rigid shock replacement for their <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/cervelo-zfs-5-carbon-full-suspension-xc-mountain-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">new ZFS-5 fully</a>… a link to lock out the frame… a LinkLock.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tech Detail </h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-race-ready.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-race-ready-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Cervelo ZFS-5 LinkLock prototype lockout gadget, XCO full-suspension to XCC hardtail conversion, short-track race-ready\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-race-ready-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-race-ready-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-race-ready-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-race-ready-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-race-ready-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-race-ready-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-race-ready.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Cervélo ZFS LinkLock is a relatively simple piece of CNC-machined 7000-series aluminum, engineered to accommodate the specific loads exerted on the frame while off-road racing with effectively no movement or loss of rider energy input. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_regaulr-RockShox-SIDLuxe-shock-and-linkage.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"444\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_regaulr-RockShox-SIDLuxe-shock-and-linkage-800x444.jpg\" alt=\"Cervelo ZFS-5 LinkLock prototype lockout gadget, XCO full-suspension to XCC hardtail conversion, with shock\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_regaulr-RockShox-SIDLuxe-shock-and-linkage-800x444.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_regaulr-RockShox-SIDLuxe-shock-and-linkage-297x165.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_regaulr-RockShox-SIDLuxe-shock-and-linkage-120x67.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_regaulr-RockShox-SIDLuxe-shock-and-linkage-768x427.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_regaulr-RockShox-SIDLuxe-shock-and-linkage-1536x853.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_regaulr-RockShox-SIDLuxe-shock-and-linkage.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Just bolt it into the same mounts as the shock &amp; short link. It’s meant to be stiff and unmoving, leaving any flex or bump absorption to the carbon frame.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_alloy-link-with-flip-chip.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_alloy-link-with-flip-chip-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Cervelo ZFS-5 LinkLock prototype lockout gadget, XCO full-suspension to XCC hardtail conversion, without shock, with geometry flip-chip\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_alloy-link-with-flip-chip-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_alloy-link-with-flip-chip-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_alloy-link-with-flip-chip-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_alloy-link-with-flip-chip-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_alloy-link-with-flip-chip-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_alloy-link-with-flip-chip-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_alloy-link-with-flip-chip.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Interestingly, this one functional alloy prototype was made with what amounts to a flip-chip insert at its attachment point to the end of the seatstays. This allowed the team to experiment a bit with the geometry of the ‘locked-out’ full-suspension hardtail. Did they want to replicate the position of the fully-extended unloaded shock. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-tuning.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-tuning-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Cervelo ZFS-5 LinkLock prototype lockout gadget, XCO full-suspension to XCC hardtail conversion, short-track tuning\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-tuning-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-tuning-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-tuning-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-tuning-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-tuning-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-tuning-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_short-track-tuning.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Instead, Milan Vader raced the Nové Město na Moravě World Cup XCC short-track race in the forward flip-chip position that more accurately preserves the geometry of the bike as it would be at proper suspension sag.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>What’s Next?</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_Milan-Vader.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_Milan-Vader-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Cervelo ZFS-5 LinkLock prototype lockout gadget, XCO full-suspension to XCC hardtail conversion, Milan Vader Jumbo-Visma\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_Milan-Vader-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_Milan-Vader-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_Milan-Vader-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_Milan-Vader-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_Milan-Vader-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_Milan-Vader-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_Milan-Vader.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Neither Jumbo-Visma nor Cervélo see the LinkLock as a realistic consumer product, but that doesn’t mean they’ll stop development work on it. I spoke with both Cervélo’s XC product manager and Milan himself today, and both seem passionate &amp; willing to try out new ideas on the path to innovating cross-country race bikes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_complete-race-bikes.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"480\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_complete-race-bikes-800x480.jpg\" alt=\"Cervelo ZFS-5 LinkLock prototype lockout gadget, XCO full-suspension to XCC hardtail conversion, bikes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_complete-race-bikes-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_complete-race-bikes-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_complete-race-bikes-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_complete-race-bikes-768x461.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_complete-race-bikes-1536x922.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Cervelo-ZFS-5-LinkLock-prototype-lockout-gadget_XCO-full-suspension-to-XCC-hardtail-conversion_complete-race-bikes.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And there will be another generation of the LinkLock. Next up will probably be a 3D-printed version, topology-optimized to shave weight off this aluminum version. The team will likely keep playing with the idea as long as World Cup courses necessitate a full-suspension XC bike for the longer XCO racing while a theoretical hardtail could be a better fit for the XCO short track.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.cervelo.com/en-US\" target=\"_blank\">Cervelo.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/cervelo-linklock-converts-xco-zfs-5-full-suspension-xc-mtb-bike-into-xcc-hardtail/\">Cervélo LinkLock Lockout Turns ZFS-5 XC Bike into a Hardtail for XCC Short Track Racing</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"1b76cb12021e057292cd0477aa3393a4fc558bc7fd2a7e1fb0b5238d135d4e49","category":"Cycling"}